cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of categorizing human actions in videos using spatiotemporal features. The use of bag of words (BoWs) models and histograms of optical flow also suggests a focus on computer vision. The paper also proposes a method for embedding SPD manifolds to Euclidean spaces, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of covariance matrices and Riemannian geometry could also suggest a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
